```plantuml
@startuml llvm_torch-mlir

[PyTorch Model] as PyTorch
[TorchScript] as TorchScript
[FX Graph] as FXGraph
[ONNX Model] as ONNX

package "Torch-MLIR" {
  [Tracing Frontend (LTC)] as TracingFrontend
  [TorchScript Importer] as TSImporter
  [FX Graph Importer] as FXImporter
  [ONNX Importer] as ONNXImporter
  
  [Torch Dialect] as TorchDialect
  [TMTensor Dialect] as TMTensorDialect
  [TorchConversion Dialect] as TorchConvDialect
  
  [Transformation Passes] as Passes
  
  [Backend Contract] as BackendContract
  
  [Linalg-on-Tensors Backend] as LinalgBackend
  [TOSA Backend] as TOSABackend
  [StableHLO Backend] as StableHLOBackend
  [LTC Backend] as LTCBackend
}

PyTorch --> TracingFrontend
TorchScript --> TSImporter
FXGraph --> FXImporter
ONNX --> ONNXImporter

TracingFrontend --> TorchDialect
TSImporter --> TorchDialect
FXImporter --> TorchDialect
ONNXImporter --> TorchDialect

TorchDialect --> Passes
TMTensorDialect --> Passes
TorchConvDialect --> Passes

Passes --> BackendContract

BackendContract --> LinalgBackend
BackendContract --> TOSABackend
BackendContract --> StableHLOBackend
BackendContract --> LTCBackend

note right of BackendContract
  Defines requirements for backends:
  - Value semantics
  - Known shapes/dtypes
end note

note right of Passes
  Key passes:
  - Reify Shape/Dtype Calculations
  - Adjust Calling Conventions
  - Globalize Object Graph
  - Fuse Quantized Ops
  - Scalarize Shapes
  - Lower To Backend Contract
end note

@enduml
```